cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CC, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes mobile web data to understand how different cohorts of the population consume news media content through their smartphones. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also a likely category as the paper addresses the issue of inequalities in the access to information and how socio-demographic factors impact the preferences and habits of the users. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) could be a possible category as the paper may involve software development for data collection and analysis. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve analyzing the complexity of the algorithms used for data analysis. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve studying how users interact with news media content on their smartphones.
